content: Hard to believe this is the same developer who gave us New York Mysteries, which I really enjoyed (all of them). I find this game tedious. I enjoy more "of this world" games. I bought the full version, but I'm not even sure I'll finish it.
Another great game ... I've played this 2 times now and I know in a year or so I'll play it two more times. Great story line with interesting puzzles that captivate. Love it!
Disappointing. The story was very episodic with a lot of 'busy work' tasks. The authors really need to have a native English speaker check the dialogue; some of it was nonsensical

Non-existent customer service ! Downloaded free game, tried to purchase hints, but none of the purchase buttons work. Clicking on any of them makes a "click" sound, but nothing happens. Multiple emails to their Customer Support went unanswered. Decided to buy full version for $6.99 - which is cheaper in the end. Had a problem there too! Completed a puzzle, but it would not let me proceed, no matter what I did. And again - NO response to emails! I really liked the game, too. What a waste of time!
Beautiful and nice game though not as good as all previous ones. Still enjoyed, just a little disappointed.
Another great game from Five-BN games

This was such a great game it was very well made and kept my intrest. I liked the story the puzzles were fun and the hidden object scenes were an original concept not the same boring style. Well worth buying and playing.

content: I played $6.99 for the full game and it was money well spent! I was thrilled to see a new release. Custom settings, morphing objects, collectibles, map, and strategy guide make this another perfect game in the Legacy series. I would love to see more games released than one or two a year, but I would rather wait for an epic adventure than to play subpar junk like BigFish and Artifex Mundi churn out all too frequently. content: Youve done it again! This game is a 10++. Too many features to detail here. Well worth the price of admission. Thanks 5BN
A little pricey but costs every cent. A descent sequel of the serie. Liked it much.
5 BN is my favorite developer. I like how some of the things from Lost Lands "tied in". I hope these games/stories never end!
another great game. really enjoyed it. prices are getting crazy even for a game of this strength and quality.
